# Walkthrough - Frontend Modernization & Multilingual Support

I have successfully upgraded the UrbanRide AI Support System frontend to a modern, production-ready design and integrated a language selector.

## Changes Made

### 🎨 Modern UI Implementation
Implemented a clean, professional dark theme using Tailwind CSS 4:
- **Background**: Modern gradient from `#0f172a` to `#1e293b`.
- **Glassmorphism**: Applied `bg-white/10` and `backdrop-blur-md` across headers, bot bubbles, and inputs.
- **Message Bubbles**: Styled user bubbles with a vibrant blue gradient and bot bubbles with a soft glass effect.
- **Improved Components**: Redesigned the sidebar, input bar, and action buttons for better UX and visual hierarchy.

### 🌍 Multilingual Support
- **Language Selector**: Added a dropdown (EN/HI/MR) in the chat header.
- **API Integration**: Updated the frontend to pass the selected language to the backend API.
- **Frontend Logic**: Updated [App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sahil/Desktop/taxi_support_bot/frontend/src/App.tsx) and [api.ts](file:///c:/Users/sahil/Desktop/taxi_support_bot/frontend/src/services/api.ts) to manage language state and include it in request payloads.

### 🛠 TypeScript & Type Safety
- **ChatHeader Types**: Fixed a TypeScript error by explicitly defining [ChatHeaderProps](file:///c:/Users/sahil/Desktop/taxi_support_bot/frontend/src/components/ChatHeader/ChatHeader.tsx#1-6) as a `type` and ensuring the component correctly receives [language](file:///c:/Users/sahil/Desktop/taxi_support_bot/app/services/language_service.py#1-4) and `setLanguage` props.
- **Global Types**: Updated [types/index.ts](file:///c:/Users/sahil/Desktop/taxi_support_bot/frontend/src/types/index.ts) to support the new multilingual API and action labels.

